New tool lets regular folks invest, benefiting 'The Speakeasy' 
July 14, 2016
The immersive theater experience "The Speakeasy" might be set in the 1920s, but its funding mechanism, equity crowdfunding, just came into being in 2016. Made legal through Regulation CF of 2012's Jumpstart Our Business Startups Act, but available to the public as an investment option only since May 16, equity crowdfunding allows anyone, not just accredited investors, to invest in a company or project.
