INVEST IN THE FUTURE OF ENTERTAINMENT
This isn't a Kickstarter project. When you invest in Legion M you aren't buying a DVD, you're buying stock in the company.





HOW DOES LEGION M MAKE MONEY?


Legion M partners with creators -- from independent filmmakers to big Hollywood studios -- to produce movies, TV shows, VR experiences and more.  We provide development support, financial backing, marketing muscle and, most importantly, fan engagement and monetization.

We're using proven business models for content production and adding a twist that gives us a competitive advantage. That's because getting fans involved in projects makes those projects more likely to succeed when they are released. 

Whether you're a producer pitching a show to a TV network, a studio trying to drive audience to the theater, or an up-and-coming Youtuber trying to break out of the basement, having a legion of fans behind you can mean the difference between success and failure. The power of Legion M is the Legion. The bigger the we get, the more valuable we become.
        


WHAT SORT OF RETURN CAN I EXPECT?
As with any investment, it's impossible to say what will happen in the future. But we can tell you what we hope to achieve. Entertainment is a massive $800 billion/year  (and growing) global industry. We believe Legion M is the sort of idea that can transform it. 

You are buying in at a $15.4MM pre-money valuation. The media companies we aspire to become (e.g. Legendary Entertainment, Vice Media, Maker Studios) are generally valued in billions. If we are successful, there is a LOT of upside.

The stock you are buying has the exact same financial terms as the founders. We're all in this together -- we only make money if you make money. We're swinging for the fences, and aiming for a return of 10x - 100x or higher for our investors. And while no one can guarantee success, we're doing everything in our power to make this the best investment you've ever made.





JOIN US


When you invest in a startup, you are investing in a vision. You are LITERALLY creating jobs, altering the course of the future, and making your mark on history. Every great company -- from Walt Disney to Facebook -- started with entrepreneurs and investors who were crazy enough to try something no one else had done before.

We believe fan-owned entertainment is an idea that's time has come. We're investing our time, money, blood, sweat, and tears to build something truly revolutionary. If you share our vision, please join the legion and help make it a reality!


Not sure if you want to invest? Join as a free member to get access members-only benefits and see for yourself what Legion M is all about.
Join the Legion for Free!


Current Projects

      When you invest in Legion M you're not just backing a single project, you are investing in an entire slate. By diversifying across different genres, mediums (i.e. TV vs. Movies), and risk profiles (i.e. high risk early-stage vs. low risk late-stage), we're building a company designed to stand the test of time. Below are some of the projects we have in active development.








Colossal

                Legion M is teaming up with NEON's Tim League and Tom Quinn to help bring Nacho Vigalondo’s wildly imaginative film COLOSSAL to market. Starring Anne Hathaway and Jason Sudeikis, COLOSSAL invades theaters this spring. Read more about Colossal.



ICONS: Face-to-Face

                In January of 2017, Legion M filmed the pilot episode of the ICONS series featuring the legendary Stan Lee. ICONS is a first-of-its-kind virtual reality interview series that allows fans to stand face to face with the luminaries, titans and leaders of our time. Read more about ICONS.










The Field Guide to Evil

               Legion M joins Christos V. Konstantakopoulos (“Before Midnight,” “The Lobster”), and Keith and Jess Calder (“Anomalisa,” “Blair Witch,” “You’re Next”) as executive producers of "Field Guide to Evil", the highly anticipated follow-up from the creators of the cult classic ABCs of Death series. Read more about The Field Guide to Evil.






Legion M Pitch Elevator

               Last fall, Legion M built a full-size elevator set on the floor of Stan Lee's Los Angeles Comic Con. Guests were invited to step inside and give a 2 minute pitch for a film, TV, or VR experience, competing for a chance to win a development deal. Today, Legion M is using this concept as the basis for an unscripted TV or Web Series. Read more about Pitch Elevator.





